Summary: I saw a brightly lit cigar-shaped flew overhead at an incredible rate of speed making no noise.
divs: Sighting DetailsI was out walking my dogs on the lake (Lake Michigan) a large bright light in the night sky caught my attention. It was if from nowhere a brigthly lit cigar-shaped object appeared from over the water. At first I thought that the object was an airplane, but it didn't display any of the usual aircraft directional lights, it's lights were solid white, and it made no noise as it passed overhead in a north-easterly direction, and moved faster than any plane that I've ever seen, and was out of sight in a matter of seconds.
